text: Kabanovsky Village Council is a municipality in the Ust-Kalmansky District of the Altai Krai in Russia. It has the status of a rural settlement and an administrative-territorial entity. The administrative center is the village of Kabanovo. == Population == According to the results of the 2010 All-Russian Population Census, the population of the municipality was 1,558 people.
